, [[Staffordshire]]. The school also had a sixth-form for young people aged 16\u201318, which closed in 2019.<ref name=\"FCS\"/>\n\n==History==\nUntil September 2011, the school was known as James Brindley Science College. In 2011 it became an academy as part of the [[Ormiston Academies Trust]].{{cn|date=March 2019}}\n\nThe school was the first academy in the country to set up a new [[sixth form]], in 2013. Although as these student finish A-levels, the sixth form is being disbanded. <ref name=\"STL\">{{cite news |last1=McInnes |first1=Kathie |title=Two schools consult on closing their sixth forms |url=https://www.stokesentinel.co.uk/news/stoke-on-trent-news/two-schools-consult-closing-sixth-864927 |accessdate=13 March 2019 |work=Stoke-on-Trent Live |date=2 December 2017}}</ref>\n\n==New building==\nThe previous buildings were in a state of disrepair and a new building was built on the site of an old hospital. This was opened in 2013 and provides space for more pupils, including post-16.{{cn|date=March 2019}}\n\n[[File:Con-113.jpg|thumb|left|Construction of the new academy building as of March 2012]] [[File:Con-118.jpg|thumb|right|Construction of the new academy building as of March 2012]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.ormistonhorizonacademy.co.uk/ Official website]\n*[http://www.jamesbrindley.stoke.sch.uk/ Old school website]\n\n{{Schools in Staffordshire}}\n{{Ormiston Academies}}\n\n[[Category:Academies in Stoke-on-Trent]]\n[[Category:Secondary schools in Stoke-on-Trent]]\n[[Category:Ormiston Academies]]\n\n\n{{Staffordshire-school-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2013}}\n{{Use British English|date=November 2013}}\n{{more citations needed|date=October 2018}}\n\n{{Infobox UK school \n| name          = Ormiston Horizon Academy\n| image         = Ormiston_Horizon_Academy_Logo.jpg\n| caption       = The Current logo used since 2011\n| motto         = Respect, Excellence, Friendship\n| established   = \n| closed